<h2 id="the-approach-two-tokens--a-blacklist">The approach: two tokens + a blacklist</h2>

<p>The solution I landed on uses two tokens instead of one:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Access token</strong> â€” lives for 15 minutes, sent on every request</li>
  <li><strong>Refresh token</strong> â€” lives for 7 days, only used to get a new access token</li>
</ul>

<p>Short-lived access tokens limit the damage if one gets stolen. 
And when the user logs out, the refresh token goes into a Redis 
